description:
Many of us have heard of Jesus - He walked this earth and lived among us. However, Jesus’ existence did not begin when He came to this earth. More than being the Son of Man, Jesus is also God and the Son of God.

"In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God. He was in the beginning with God. All things were made through Him, and without Him, nothing was made that was made. In Him was life, and the life was the light of men. And the light shines in the darkness, and the darkness did not comprehend it" (John 1:1-5).

Jesus is our Creator, our Savior, and our Judge. 

Listen to Pastor Ted Wilson’s message as he uses the Scriptures to explain, “God the Son, Who Is He?” https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=--IbCqUMVpw&list=PL-k2Gb-DBYo_ANrUJhHN2_4bSlMDTjuqQ&index=43
